          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">My Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName role="author">A Rice</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>.<date>July</date>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p><hi rend="underline">post paid</hi> in <placeName><hi
                                                  rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>,
                                                  <date>Monday</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sivan (May),
                                                  1850</date>.</p>
                              <p>My dear Sir:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Be so good as to advertise in<lb/> the next number
                                        of the “Occident,”<lb/> the notice written below, and
                                        after-<lb/>wards, send me a bill for it, and<lb/> the
                                        congregation will pay for it. I<lb/> shall write it here in
                                        German and<lb/> you will translate it correctly<lb/> into
                                        the English Language.</p>
                              <p>“The congregation of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> de-<lb/>sires
                                        to have a person who will be<lb/> able to fill completely
                                        the position<lb/> as cantor and, at the same time,<lb/> as
                                        teacher of Hebrew in a school<lb/> of 60 children. He must
                                        be quite<lb/> accomplished as cantor and<lb/> teacher. His
                                        salary will be $500.<lb/> annually. The year begins the</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p><date>first of next October</date>. No one<lb/> should present
                                        himself unless<lb/> he is able to do well in both of<lb/>
                                        these respects. All applications<lb/> must arrive post free,
                                        otherwise<lb/> they will not be accepted. They<lb/> are to
                                        be addressed to me until<lb/> the <date>first of
                                                  August</date>, as follows:<lb/>
                                        <persName role="author">Rev. A. Rice</persName>,
                                                  <placeName>North Exeter, no.<lb/> 8</placeName>.
                                        The person who is considered<lb/> fit will receive an
                                        answer<lb/> and will have to present himself<lb/> here at
                                        his own expense. He will<lb/> then be interviewed by the
                                        congrega-<lb/>tion.”</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">I am and shall always</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">remain, Most respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)"> Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Rice</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>You will include<lb/> this only in your<lb/>
                                        <date>July</date> number.</p>
                    </body>
